The terminal application is the local server that you start first. In that application thereÂ´s a helpsection if you type :h.

After the server is up and running, go ahead and start the rest of the applications. 
The server will give you messages for when an application is connected and for when something has happened in any of the applications.

Keep the customers terminal to ip 127.0.0.1.

If you dont want to use the server that is fine as the applications can run without it, but doesn`t update the view instantly.

Every application is connected to the database so any changes will go to the database even if the server isn`t running.

Those applications that requires username and password uses these credentials:

username: 1
password: admin

admin can log in to all applications
